[thinking] **Clarifying Kotlin and Java compilation**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I remember that Java sources aren't compiled with `kotlinc`, but Kotlin can reference Java compiled classes from `compileJava`. Generally, `compileJava` relies on `compileKotlin`, since Java might refer to Kotlin code. In Gradle for Kotlin JVM, `compileKotlin` runs before `compileJava`. It seems that mixed Kotlin and Java projects are indeed supported, allowing them to reference each other. Kotlin and Java can coexist; Java compiles against Kotlin outputs, and they can both be stored together in a project. This is interesting!
[thinking] 
