C-ul9tUm3wz77ebxGW_JF2uNYD0quVSQcWSrvEWbOAErKITsoqR3DVyrXdl04gJcJTEcsDGhjjamqTAySYMGtk2gxqfct-UMeAioUrVlbZ2wqLSWZPdvAb_oXlQDAtzQnBYZPjs7y02PBoJBD8BpnRtCGYPLlm3IqqWuQj6GKFhxaQtbnMMaLYXV4bPTiTKVdbOxN94eNeQj20WFTnOx68FduVNX_AA2-zHyrcBSIXsNWrWsXBbdlWWJwSKhIH13XmISEqerM8KC1bCtoAXORjBnfOc1MqZqrjgaFLOBP3Q8wIWunIVt8MjI78Ky5H9M719qvTfVGByoRysEGku7M4Pgqhei0AKhyPuE7Q2EMIefaGE4Dk5vNu8YSvteTuzy7E-l_y\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying Kotlin and Java compilation**\\n\\nI remember that Java sources aren't compiled with `kotlinc`, but Kotlin can reference Java compiled classes from `compileJava`. Generally, `compileJava` relies on `compileKotlin`, since Java might refer to Kotlin code. In Gradle for Kotlin JVM, `compileKotlin` runs before `compileJava`. It seems that mixed Kotlin and Java projects are indeed supported, allowing them to reference each other. Kotlin and Java can coexist; Java compiles against Kotlin outputs, and they can both be stored together in a project. This is interesting!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_H9J8cWQqmw9DOlhhw6LvwcBo|fc_0da4d2342ba752470169fa1b6f758c819e943a330fc4bb5168", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-main-kts/2.3.21/src/test/kotlin/org_jetbrains_kotlin/kotlin_main_kts/ConfigurationFromTemplateKtTest.kt", "edits": [{"oldText": "import kotlin.script.experimental.api.baseClass\n", "newText": ""}, {"oldText": "import kotlin.script.experimental.api.scriptsInstancesSharing\n", "newText": ""}, {"oldText": "import kotlin.script.experimental.jvmhost.createJvmScriptDefinitionFromTemplate\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport org.jetbrains.kotlin.mainKts.MainKtsScript\n", "newText": "import org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    fun createsDefinitionFromBundledMainKtsTemplate(): Unit {\n        val definition = createScriptDefinitionFromTemplate(\n            KotlinType(MainKtsScript::class),\n            scriptLoadingHostConfiguration(),\n        )\n\n        assertThat(definition.compilationConfiguration[ScriptCompilationConfiguration.fileExtension])\n            .isEqualTo(\"main.kts\")\n        assertThat(definition.compilationConfiguration[ScriptCompilationConfiguration.baseClass]?.fromClass)\n            .isEqualTo(MainKtsScript::class)\n        assertThat(definition.evaluationConfiguration[ScriptEvaluationConfiguration.scriptsInstancesSharing])\n            .isTrue()\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    fun createsJvmDefinitionFromConstructorBackedTemplate(): Unit {\n        val definition = createJvmScriptDefinitionFromTemplate<ConstructorBackedScriptTemplate>()\n\n        assertThat(definition.compilationConfiguration[ScriptCompilationConfiguration.defaultImports])\n            .containsExactly(\"java.time.Instant\")\n        assertThat(definition.evaluationConfiguration[ScriptEvaluationConfiguration.constructorArgs])\n            .containsExactly(\"evaluation constructor argument\")\n    }\n\n", "newText": ""}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 398, "output": 1347, "cacheRead": 78336, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 80081, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777998687736, "responseId": "resp_0da4d2342ba752470169fa1b60e3f0819eae25a0c101b046fa"}}
